snippet.textDisplay:
Mine is very simple. Not that I asked for it, but try it if u want to.

First cup: Make black coffee- doesn’t matter how, make it strong if I want to.... Put it in the fridge. Let cool.

Separate cup: unsweetened vanilla almond milk, brown sugar, vanilla extract, cinnamon, and a teeeeeeeennnniiiieeeee bit amount !!!!TEENSIE!!!! Bit amount of almond extract (if u want to- u don’t have to). Warm in a microwave and then mix until fully dissolved. Put in fridge


***less than 1 hour later***


Fancy mason jar: ice. Coffee from first cup. Pour milk flavor thingy into coffee (it’s really nice to look at it mixing and swirling around). Pour some liquid creamer into it if you’re a sugar freak- I am.


AND WALA!!!! There u have it. I hope u like it y’all. I have yet to try Emma’s coffee, by that’s definitely on my bucket list. Thanks Emma. 😘
